cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.LG

This paper discusses the design and implementation of consent management platforms (CMPs) in the context of the EU's General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) and "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper analyzes the impact of CMP designs on users' consent choices, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and user behavior, making "cs.HC" (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely category. The study also involves data analysis and modeling, which could fall under "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning).
